A St. Louis style BBQ sauce. 

4 slices bacon
15 mL ground ancho chile
475 mL canned whole, peeled tomatoes, pureed in blender
120 mL dark brown sugar
120 mL apple cider vinegar
60 mL whole-grain mustard
15 mL tbsp. Worcestershire sauce
15 mL kosher salt, plus more to taste
Freshly ground black pepper, to taste
4 cloves garlic, finely chopped
.25 medium onion, chopped

Adapted from Saveur (June/July 2011)

One RECIPE = ~600 mL sauce

"Heat oven to 350Â°. Heat bacon in a 4-qt. saucepan over medium heat; cook, stirring, until fat renders, about 6 minutes. Add chile powder, garlic, and onions, and cook, stirring, until soft, about 5 minutes. Add tomatoes, sugar, vinegar, mustard, Worcestershire, salt, and pepper, and bring to a boil; cook for 5 minutes. Remove from heat; set aside."
